result.execSummary:
The defendant Davonte K. HARVALA was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Conspracy to Commit Robbery with Use of Force [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant in custody and appearing by video from the Manitowoc County Jail.  The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crimes of conspiracy to commit armed robbery and PTC operate without owner's consent.  The matters are continued for initial appearance on 10-19-15 at 2:30 p.m.  Bail is set at $2,000.00 cash with the conditions that he report to the Manitowoc County Sheriff's Department for fingerprints, photographs and other identifying information within 24 hours of release and have no contact with co-defendants Nathan Holan or A.S.N., DOB: 07-13-1999 or KK Unimart in Mishicot.  Defendant is ordered to submit to a DNA sample.   Bail not furnished and defendant is remanded into custody.  Commitment for failure to furnish bail issued.  Copy filed.
